---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="The practice, engagement structures, and who it is for. Independent advisory for industrials, energy developers, and advanced manufacturers from German-speaking countries entering the US market."
>
  <article class="about">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- ── Header ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <header class="about__header">
        <p class="label">The practice</p>
        <h1 class="about__title">Christian Kameir</h1>
      </header>

      <!-- ── Photo + Bio ─────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="about__body">

        <div class="about__photo-wrap">
          <img
            src="/images/christian-kameir.jpg"
            alt="Christian Kameir"
            class="about__photo"
            width="400"
            height="500"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="about__bio prose">
          <p>
            Independent advisory based in Newport Beach, California, with an operational
            footprint in New Mexico. The practice helps capital-intensive companies —
            primarily industrials, energy developers, and advanced manufacturers from
            German-speaking countries — enter the United States market, capture the
            federal, state, and county incentives available to them, and connect with
            the private capital sources that complete the stack.
          </p>
          <p>
            Bilingual German&thinsp;/&thinsp;English. Thirty years at the intersection of
            capital, technology, and industrial operations — founding companies, backing
            them, and building the transatlantic relationships that make the work possible.
            Kameir operates what he advises on rather than consulting from the sidelines.
          </p>
          <p>
            Earlier credentials include founding and exiting Colizer Inc. (San Diego, 2009),
            three rounds of venture financing, and investment and board positions across the
            United States, United Kingdom, and Germany through M&amp;P Capital. Guest lecturer
            at Harvard on fintech and central bank digital currencies. Contributor to Forbes
            and HackerNoon. Chairs the Banking &amp; Finance Special Interest Group at the
            Decentralized Identity Foundation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ── Rule ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <hr class="rule" />

      <!-- ── Engagements ─────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="about__section">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Engagement structures</h2>

        <div class="engagement">
          <div class="engagement__head">
            <span class="engagement__number">01</span>
            <h3 class="engagement__name">US-Entry Advisory</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement__desc">
            End-to-end support for companies from German-speaking countries establishing
            US operations: site selection, state and local incentive negotiation, US entity
            formation pathway, regulatory navigation, and integration with the federal
            capital stack. Six-month minimum, retained.
          </p>
          <p class="engagement__floor">$22,000&thinsp;/&thinsp;month · Six-month minimum</p>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement">
          <div class="engagement__head">
            <span class="engagement__number">02</span>
            <h3 class="engagement__name">Capital Stack Assembly</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement__desc">
            Identification, qualification, and capture across two tracks. On the public side:
            IRA tax credits, DOE loan programs, USDA REAP, DOD industrial base programs,
            state revolving funds, and county-level incentive packages. On the private side:
            warm introductions to strategic investors, family offices, project-finance lenders,
            infrastructure funds, and institutional LPs matched to the specific project stage
            and structure.
          </p>
          <p class="engagement__floor">Retainer plus success fee on captured capital</p>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement">
          <div class="engagement__head">
            <span class="engagement__number">03</span>
            <h3 class="engagement__name">Fractional Executive and Board Advisory</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement__desc">
            Operating-bench role for US ventures and companies from German-speaking countries
            expanding stateside that need a senior US-resident operator without a full executive
            hire. Cash plus equity.
          </p>
          <p class="engagement__floor">$18,000&thinsp;/&thinsp;month · Twelve-month minimum</p>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement">
          <div class="engagement__head">
            <span class="engagement__number">04</span>
            <h3 class="engagement__name">Project-Plus-Retainer</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement__desc">
            Hybrid structure for transactions with a defined closing event — acquisitions,
            financings, JV stand-ups — combining a project fee at signing with an ongoing
            retainer through the post-close integration window.
          </p>
          <p class="engagement__floor">Project fee at signing · Retainer through integration</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Rule ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <hr class="rule" />

      <!-- ── Problems solved ─────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="about__section">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">What the practice solves</h2>
        <div class="prose prose--wide">
          <p>
            The decision-to-production lead time for an industrial from a German-speaking
            country entering the US is eighteen to twenty-four months. Most of that time
            is lost in the first six: wrong site selected, wrong incentive structure pursued,
            federal capital window missed, private capital conversations started too late or
            with the wrong counterparties, US legal entity built in a way that blocks the
            credits the company was counting on.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="failures">
          <div class="failure">
            <h3 class="failure__title">Timing</h3>
            <p>
              State incentive funds are annual budget pools that close when full. IRA tax
              credits step down on construction-start schedules. Companies that treat 2026
              as a planning year typically miss the 2026 capital cycle entirely and reset
              to 2027.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="failure">
            <h3 class="failure__title">Structure</h3>
            <p>
              The site selected, the entity stood up, and the financing path chosen are
              interdependent decisions. Treating them sequentially — choose the site, then
              go look for capital — forecloses the most valuable options. Kameir runs them
              in parallel from the start.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="failure">
            <h3 class="failure__title">Intermediated incentives</h3>
            <p>
              Most US site-selection advisors are paid by the receiving state or county,
              which means the advice tracks where the referral fee is largest, not where
              the project belongs. Kameir is paid only by the client.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="failure">
            <h3 class="failure__title">The operator gap</h3>
            <p>
              Most advisory firms hand a deck to a client and walk away from execution.
              Kameir takes engagements only at the level of involvement at which the
              work actually gets done.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Rule ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <hr class="rule" />

      <!-- ── Who fits ────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="about__section">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Who fits the practice</h2>
        <div class="prose prose--wide">
          <p>
            Decision makers who fit the practice are typically founders, CEOs, CFOs, board
            members, family-office principals, and PE deal leads with budget authority at or
            above $15,000 per month and a live decision in front of them — not a research project.
          </p>
          <p>
            Kameir qualifies prospective clients rather than the reverse: fit is assessed on the
            live situation, the counterpart's decision authority, and the alignment of scope with
            the current engagement roster. Not every inquiry receives an offer, and not every offer
            is accepted — that is how the practice stays useful to the clients already on the roster.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Rule ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <hr class="rule" />

      <!-- ── Practice anchors ────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="about__section">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Practice anchors</h2>
        <dl class="about__dl">
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>Engagement floor</dt>
            <dd>$18,000&thinsp;/&thinsp;month ($22,000&thinsp;/&thinsp;month for US-entry onshoring)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>Minimums</dt>
            <dd>Six months on capital and onshoring engagements. Twelve months on fractional advisory.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>Payment terms</dt>
            <dd>Net-15. First month on signature.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>Referral fees</dt>
            <dd>None from US states, counties, or site-selection intermediaries.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>Not offered</dt>
            <dd>Contingent-only structures. Grant ghost-writing of record. Free consultations, capability decks, or proposals below engagement floor.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Education ────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <hr class="rule" />
      <section class="about__section">
        <h2 class="about__section-title">Education</h2>
        <dl class="about__dl">
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>University of Münster</dt>
            <dd>Master of Law</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>University of Oxford</dt>
            <dd>Old English &amp; English Literature</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>University of Bielefeld</dt>
            <dd>Literature and Linguistics</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="about__dl-item">
            <dt>University of Munich</dt>
            <dd>Legal Forensic Studies</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Contact CTA ──────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="about__contact-cta">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Request a call</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
/* ── Header ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about__header {
  padding-top: 4rem;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.about__title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.75rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
}

/* ── Photo + Bio ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about__body {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 230px 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-l);
  align-items: start;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.about__photo-wrap {
  position: sticky;
  top: 2rem;
}

.about__photo {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 1px;
  display: block;
  background: var(--bg-subtle);
  aspect-ratio: 4/5;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center top;
  filter: grayscale(10%);
}

.about__bio {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
}

/* ── Sections ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about__section {
  margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.about__section-title {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
}

/* ── Engagements ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
.engagement {
  padding-bottom: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.engagement:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.engagement__head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.engagement__number {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.engagement__name {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0;
}

.engagement__desc {
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  max-width: 680px;
}

.engagement__floor {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  color: var(--text-muted);
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

/* ── Failures ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.prose--wide {
  max-width: 680px;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
}

.failures {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
  margin-top: var(--space-m);
}

.failure__title {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
}

.failure p {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

/* ── Definition list ──────────────────────────────────────── */
.about__dl {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.1rem;
}

.about__dl-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
  gap: 1rem;
  align-items: baseline;
}

.about__dl-item dt {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text);
}

.about__dl-item dd {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ── Contact CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
.about__contact-cta {
  padding-block: var(--space-l);
}

/* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .about__body {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .about__photo-wrap {
    position: static;
    max-width: 200px;
  }

  .about__dl-item {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .failures {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
}
</style>
